# AKOS HLK SSOT mirror — external repo cursor rule

> **Template location:** `.cursor/rules/akos-mirror-template.mdc` in the AKOS repo (this file).
> **Instance location:** copied as `.cursor/rules/akos-mirror.mdc` to the root of each external Holistika-tracked repository that has a `.cursor/rules/` directory. Boilerplate has no `.cursor/rules/` today and so does not receive this file (per D-IH-32-N: light-touch reference-only).

## What this rule says (always-apply on every cursor session)

This repository is governed by the AKOS HLK doctrine. The Single Source of Truth for HLK content (process_list, baseline_organisation, all compliance.* mirrors, KM Topic-Fact-Source, brand voice, localisation policy, the 6-axis Holistik Ops doctrine) is the AKOS repo, not this one.

**Live references:**

- AKOS repository: `https://github.com/FraysaXII/openclaw-akos`
- HLK vault: `https://github.com/FraysaXII/openclaw-akos/tree/main/docs/references/hlk/v3.0/`
- Compliance canonicals: `https://github.com/FraysaXII/openclaw-akos/tree/main/docs/references/hlk/compliance/`
- Precedence ledger: `https://github.com/FraysaXII/openclaw-akos/blob/main/docs/references/hlk/compliance/PRECEDENCE.md`
- 6-axis doctrine: `https://github.com/FraysaXII/openclaw-akos/blob/main/docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/Operations/PMO/HOLISTIK_OPS_DISCOVERY.md`

GitHub URLs are stable; local paths to a developer's AKOS clone vary.

## On conflict, AKOS wins

If a doctrine statement in this repository's local docs (e.g., `docs/data_policies/`, `documentation/`, `other_documentation/`) disagrees with the AKOS canonical, **AKOS is correct**. Open a PR to AKOS to update the canonical; do not edit the local doc to "match" by writing a new local rule.

## Never invent HLK IDs locally

Do not create new `persona_id`, `channel_id`, `vendor_id`, `skill_id`, `cell_id`, `policy_id`, `program_id`, `topic_id`, GOI/POI `ref_id`, `process item_id`, `org_id`, or any other governed identifier locally.

To add a new ID: open a PR against the AKOS canonical CSV (e.g. `docs/references/hlk/compliance/dimensions/SKILL_REGISTRY.csv` for a new skill).

## Brand-jargon audit applies to all external prose

External-facing prose in this repository (public README sections, deployed web pages, deck slides, generated dossiers, cover emails) must not contain forbidden tokens from `BRAND_JARGON_AUDIT.md` §4: internal codenames (`AKOS`, `topic_*`, `plane`), stack jargon (`RBAC`, `RLS`, `pgvector`, `FDW`, `kirbe.*` — except where it is the literal schema name in code), methodology shorthand (`KM`, `MASTER`), operator-side process tokens (`TODO[OPERATOR-x]`, `dtp_`).

Internal prose (developer code comments, implementation notes, internal SOPs) is unrestricted.

